// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// STAGE 8C-4 — HERO COMBO A "MERIDIAN LOOP" live-game integration.
//
// The SECOND Hero sword combo (the first, DAYBREAK CHAIN, ships in heroCombo1..4
// and is NOT touched here). Where Daybreak is a combo of ARCS pivoting on the body,
// MERIDIAN is a combo of LINES that crosses the arena and loops back:
//
//   S1 SUNSTEP      grounded shallow-bow sword opener
//   S2 ZENITH DIVE  vertical launch -> ECLIPSE apex -> rotating Light-Eclipse dive
//                   -> planted floor slam
//   S3 SUNGLAIVE    the light leaves the sword: a thrown slash projectile
//   S4 CHASECUT     stores THE MARK, then cuts forward ~5 hero lengths (the chase)
//   S5 NOON PILLAR  a world-scale Light-Eclipse pillar at the far end, then the Hero
//      + ECHO RETURN unmakes and reforms back AT THE MARK while the pillar still burns
//
// This module is the self-contained sequence CONTROLLER + its data. It is the
// approved Stage 8C-0 REV 2 art, packaged in the Stage 8C-2 handoff
// (tools/redesign/hero_combo_a_*), wired here as an ADDITIONAL Hero attack variant.
// Enemy.js selects it occasionally in place of the 4-hit combo and delegates its
// update/draw/cleanup to this controller; nothing about the existing combo, the
// FSM's COMBO.HITS phase-indexing, Boss, Dragon Wrath or Combo B is changed.
//
// SOURCE OF TRUTH: tools/redesign/hero_combo_a_literal.txt (validated by
// hero_combo_a_validate.js — 36 checks). The 5 body clips + 4 detached world-space
// grids below are cell-for-cell that literal (a build step injects them verbatim and
// a byte-compare proves fidelity). Do NOT hand-edit the matrix data — regenerate.
//
// Body clips are 44x34 (hero base at 7,10; feet row 33) — the SAME canvas as
// DAYBREAK, so the proven Enemy.draw path serves them (frame.length >= 20 ->
// HERO_REDESIGN_PALETTE @ HERO_IDLE_PIXEL). Effects are BAKED into the body frames.
// The four detached grids (glaive / corridor / pillar / reform) are PURE LIGHT keys
// and are world-space effects painted by drawWorldEffects() at world coordinates —
// they do NOT ride the sprite anchor.
//
// RENDER-ONLY LAW for the detached grids: they never carry a hitbox. The only
// damaging boxes Combo A uses are the shared attackHitbox (S1 / S2 / S4 strikes, via
// the existing convention) and one Combo-A-owned slash projectile (S3, via the
// existing projectiles[] seam) — both scoped local and reported in the handoff.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

